          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Boulder, CO 4/7/02  Directors Cut<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.78)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=6076'>Joseph "marinethrawn" Diniega</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=6076&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 8, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Well, this is the second tourney that I am running up here in Boulder. Mainly most of the tournaments here in Colorado are in Parker and in Colorado Springs. There is some other ones here and there in Denver and in like Pueblo and stuff, however, we want to get Boulder a bigger place for LOTR. So this is the 4th tourney in Boulder, I ran one earlier and John Arendt ran the other 2. We have some other tourney directors up here so we plan to start making tournaments biweekly (or as often as we can). <br>
<br>
Anyway, Friday night, I played some with my friends, so we were testing out our decks and I am going with my Gandalf, Aragorn fellowship that I played the week before, and then Moria swarms with cave trolls for shadow. Now the reason that I am getting decks ready is that last tourney I ran, we only had 7 so I had to play to make it sanctioned. I just wanted to prepare incase the same situation came up again. And yes, for those of you who don’t know, the tournament director can play if there are less than 16 participants and at least 2 other TD’s playing in the tourney(I think it was 2 TD’s, but anyways). Well, I end up playing JK:2 Jedi Outcast all Friday night after we play LOTR. That game is so fun, if there is a computer game to get, that is it. Well, I am stuck on the stupid part where the Admiral has all the armor and you have to destroy his shields, so if any of you can give hints, let me know. Anyway, I go to bed at like 12:30, then get up 5 hours later cause for ROTC, we have a Rifle/Pistol competition and since I am on the pistol team, and our school is hosting, we have to be there early to set up. Well we set up and the other schools come (University of Kansas NROTC, University of Oklahoma NROTC, Ohio State University NROTC, etc.) and we have are briefs and then get to shooting. Well to make a long story short, we won. Then we went out and celebrated that night, however, some of my friends and I got back early so we could get out decks ready for the tourney, since they wanted to play some more. Well, we set our clocks ahead an hour for daylight savings time and then went to bed at like 1. We got up at 9:30 (this is the most I got in a long time) and then got ready and headed to Dragonfire games where I was hosting it. We were the first ones there so I put out the command cards and then set up. About 5 minutes later, my brother (the onespoon), Scott Gaeta, and Mark Ponting show up. Then John Arendt shows up after that. Well I got a call from Joe Helfrich and he says he is going to be late. So when he shows up, we have 7, so it looks like I have to play. We start the tourney at like 11:45. <br>
<br>
Game one: Me verses Dan Bellinghausen, mixed fellowship and Moria <br>
<br>
Well this is one of my friends and we pretty much already know who is going to win. He goes first, starts the pony and gets out Aragorn. He moves to site 2, I put out some guys and deal like 2 wounds. He decides to stays. I play Aragorn and Legolas from hand, Aragorn’s bow, and an Armor and then double to site 3 cause he doesn’t get much out. He then moves to 3 and gives me like 4 so I can’t do anything. He stays. It then move to 4, he gets out some guys and I kill all but 1 with directed archery, and then Gandalf takes a wound. I decide to stay. He plays some stuff then moves to 4 and I get out some guys and I think that is when I killed of pippen. Well, he stays so it is my turn. I then play Boromir and Armor and move to the bridge. Like 2 small guys and the balrog comes out. Basically I kill the small guys and Boromir takes two wounds. I then decide to stay. His turn he moves to site 5, I don’t remember exactly what happened but the balrog and the cavetroll comes out along with a lot of other guys. Basically only Frodo and someone else survive, he stays. I then move to site 6 and nothing happens, I stay to heal my wounds. His turn, moves to site 6 and well, I get out enough to overwhelm Frodo. <br>
<br>
FW (+3) <br>
<br>
Well now some else just showed up late so he jumps in and I drop so that there is no bye. Scott won his first game, along with my brother, and Michael King. Not much happened really then for the second game. My brother won again, along with Scott, John Arendt, and Joe Helfrich. Well now someone else shows up and he jumps in, so I jump back in so there is no bye again. <br>
<br>
Game 3 (2 for me): Me vs. Dennis Toprac Something fellowship and Uruh-kai <br>
<br>
Well we both bid 0 and I go first. I get out Aragorn and Boromir. He then puts out 2 Uruh-kai and I put up Gandalf and Boromir. Boromir takes his 2 wounds, but then he has some adders and Gandalf bites the dust. Luckily the deck is more based around Aragorn. I stop at site 2. He the plays some guys and moves, I get out one thing, and he beats it. Then moves to 3 and I play nothing. My turn I just move and give him 3 so can’t do anything. I stay, his turn, he moves to 4, I have a full shadow had, so I play nothing, cause it is all expensive. He decides to move again, and then I drop everything and the Balrog. Only Boromir and Frodo Survived. In my turn I played the bow on Aragorn and Legolas and then moved to site 4, he gets out like 2 guys and I beat them both. He then moves to site 6 and I get out some more guys and overwhelm Boromir, so now he is down to just Frodo. My turn, I move to the bridge and he plays Lurtz and some other guys. I kill the Lurtz with archery and then beat one guy and take a wound from the other guy. I stay. He moves to site 7 and then I just drop more stuff and overwhelm Frodo. <br>
<br>
FW (+6) <br>
<br>
Now things are starting to get interesting. <br>
<br>
Game 4 (3 for me): Me vs. The Onespoon (my brother) Super fellowship and Moria heavy swarm <br>
<br>
This game was bad for both of us since the beginning. For the first 4 my brother only sees 1 goblin runner for shadow and I get minimal minions plus get this, I have a 60 card draw deck, have 4 Aragorn’s and 4 Cave trolls, I don’t see any of them till site 6. We both just jumped sites in the beginning, and the Balrog really did nothing. My brother though never got his armors out so he had to take 2 wounds on Aragorn and 2 on boromir. Then in the later sites, we finally started getting out shadow, and it became a race to 9. I move to 7 first, then stay. He doubles to 8, and I get like everyone exhausted but no one dies. I then move to 8, but he gets out 5 orcs and I can’t move again, even though I beat them all. So now it is all depended on my shadow, which I don’t get a lot in my hand. He moves to 9 and has 3 burdens so I draw 3 cards, I get 2 more minions, and I am down to like 3 cards in my deck. I play 2 armories and then 5 guys, and a scimitar, scavengers, play him, scimitar from lost and draw another. A free peeps card. I then discard 3 and get out another from my lost deck. So 7 guys to his 5. He tries to archer 2 away but the armories save them. I have to put the guys on Frodo, and he doesn’t have a paths, so I pull off a close game. <br>
<br>
FW (+9) <br>
<br>
Well, the guy who showed up at game 3 had to leave, so I drop again to not create a bye. Why the guy came for 2 games, who knows, but anyways, I watch all the games. The final results are like this: <br>
<br>
1 - William Diniega (+13) <br>
2 – John Arendt (+11) <br>
3 – Joe Helfrich (+11) <br>
4 – Scott Gaeta (+9) <br>
5 – Mike King (+9) <br>
6 – Dan Bellinghausen (+9) <br>
7 – Mark Ponting (+9) <br>
8 – Joseph Diniega (+9, hey, I only played 3 games) <br>
9 – Bas Hamer (+6) <br>
10 – Dennis Toprac (+2, but dropped) <br>
<br>
Pros: <br>
Good turn out with cool people. <br>
Thanks Joe for getting the Pizza. <br>
